<p><strong>Skills</strong> Perception +3, Stealth +6</p>

<p><strong>Challenge</strong> 2 (450 XP)</p>

<p><strong><em>Keen Smell.</em></strong> The tiger has advantage on Wisdom (Perception) checks that rely on smell.</p>

<p><strong><em>Pounce.</em></strong> If the tiger moves at least 20 ft. straight toward a creature and then hits it with a claw attack on the same turn, that target must succeed on a DC 14 Strength saving throw or be knocked prone. If the target is prone, the tiger can make one bite attack against it as a bonus action.</p>

<p><strong>Actions</strong></p>

<p><strong><em>Bite.</em></strong> Melee Weapon Attack: +6 to hit, reach 5 ft., one target. Hit: 10 (1d10 + 5) piercing damage.</p>

<p><strong><em>Claw.</em></strong> Melee Weapon Attack: +6 to hit, reach 5 ft., one target. Hit: 12 (2d6 + 5) slashing damage.</p>

